 <office:body>
  <office:text text:use-soft-page-breaks="true">
   <office:forms form:automatic-focus="false" form:apply-design-mode="false"/>
   <text:sequence-decls>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Illustration"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Table"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Text"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Drawing"/>
    <text:sequence-decl text:display-outline-level="0" text:name="Figure"/>
   </text:sequence-decls>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_1" text:outline-level="1">Ulteriori sviluppi della Teoria</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Nella scheda quattro abbiamo introdotto l’equazione di Schrödinger per una particella carica in un potenziale elettrico. Questa equazione ci permette di determinare <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object6" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.8252in" svg:height="0.2055in" draw:z-index="0"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mi>ψ</mi>
           <mrow>
            <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
            <mrow>
             <mrow>
              <mi>x</mi>
              <mi>,</mi>
              <mi>y</mi>
              <mi>,</mi>
              <mi>z</mi>
              <mi>,</mi>
              <mi>t</mi>
             </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
           </mrow>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ψ left (x,y,z,t right )} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADOgEAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAJgAsAHEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       t////4AHAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgABAAAAD7Arz9CQEAAAAAkAEAAAAC
       BAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAIAAAAMgqeAXIBAQAAACgAEAAAAPsCvP0JAQAAAACQAQAA
       AAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAACAAAADIKngEhBwEAAAApABUAAAD7AkD+
       AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQAABAAAAPABAQAIAAAA
       MgqgAXQGAQAAAHQACAAAADIKoAEpBQEAAAB6AAgAAAAyCqABpgMBAAAAeQAIAAAAMgqgARUC
       AQAAAHgAFQAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAAEAgAQVGltZXMgTmV3IFJvbWFuAACDBAAAAC0B
       AQAEAAAA8AEAAAgAAAAyCqAB5gUBAAAALAAIAAAAMgqgAXgEAQAAACwACAAAADIKoAHgAgEA
       AAAsABAAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEBAAACBAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAEAAAA8AEBAAgA
       AAAyCqAB+v8BAAAAeQAKAAAAJgYPAAoA/////wEAAAAAABAAAAD7AhQACQAAAAAAvAIAAAAA
       AQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAQAEAAAA8AEAAAMAAAAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, cioè la distribuzione di ampiezze di probabilità in funzione del tempo per la terna di grandezze misurabili <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object7" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.5555in" svg:height="0.2055in" draw:z-index="1"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
           <mrow>
            <mrow>
             <mi>x</mi>
             <mi>,</mi>
             <mi>y</mi>
             <mi>,</mi>
             <mi>z</mi>
            </mrow>
           </mrow>
           <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ left (x,y,z right )} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADCgEAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAJgAmAFEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       t////yAFAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgABAAAAD7Arz9CQEAAAAAkAEAAAAC
       BAIAEFN5bWJvbAACBAAAAC0BAAAIAAAAMgqeATAAAQAAACgAEAAAAPsCvP0JAQAAAACQAQAA
       AAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAACAAAADIKngG+BAEAAAApABUAAAD7AkD+
       AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAfgQAAAAtAQAABAAAAPABAQAIAAAA
       MgqgAecDAQAAAHoACAAAADIKoAFkAgEAAAB5AAgAAAAyCqAB0wABAAAAeAAVAAAA+wJA/gAA
       AAAAAJABAAAAAAQCABBUaW1lcyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAH4EAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQAACAAAADIK
       oAE2AwEAAAAsAAgAAAAyCqABngEBAAAALAAKAAAAJgYPAAoA/////wEAAAAAABAAAAD7AhQA
       CQAAAAAAvAIAAAAAAQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAAAEAAAA8AEBAAMAAAAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>. Lo scopo centrale della presente scheda sarà quello di determinare la distribuzione di ampiezze di probabilità per altre grandezze osservabili, in particolare per la quantità di moto, per il momento angolare e per l’energia.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Per raggiungere lo scopo è necessario rivedere e generalizzare i principi della Meccanica Quantistica che abbiamo postulato nella scheda due.</text:p>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2">Principi della Meccanica Quantistica.</text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">Per comodità di lettura riportiamo qui i principi che abbiamo postulato nella scheda due:</text:p>
   <text:list text:style-name="WW8Num7">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P4">Un sistema fisico è caratterizzato dalle sue grandezze fisiche che possono essere misurate.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P4">Quando si misura una grandezza <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> sono possibili diversi risultati, ed ogni risultato ha una certa probabilità di uscire. Se dalla misura si ottiene un particolare risultato <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object8" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.35in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="2"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mover accent="true">
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
             </mover>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g= { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADzAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAmAEEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         9////yAEAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
         AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQAzAwUAAAATAlUAEwQVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
         cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAIMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABGgMBAAAAZwAIAAAAMgpgAU4AAQAAAGcA
         EAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQECAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIK
         YAGtAQEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsCFAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIi
         U3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIAAwAAAAAA
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>, il sistema si porta in uno stato tale che, se si ripete la misura di <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> si ottiene con certezza il valore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object9" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.35in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="3"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mover accent="true">
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
             </mover>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g= { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADzAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAmAEEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         9////yAEAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
         AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQAzAwUAAAATAlUAEwQVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
         cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAIMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABGgMBAAAAZwAIAAAAMgpgAU4AAQAAAGcA
         EAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQECAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIK
         YAGtAQEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsCFAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIi
         U3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIAAwAAAAAA
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>. Un tale stato viene detto autostato di <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> con autovalore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object10" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1134in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="4"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mover accent="true">
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
            </mover>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADpAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAqABEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         9////2ABAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
         AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQBnAAUAAAATAlUARwEVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
         cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAKMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABTgABAAAAZwAKAAAAJgYPAAoA/////wEA
         AAAAABAAAAD7AhQACQAAAAAAvAIAAAAAAQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAgAEAAAA8AEBAAMA
         AAAAAA==
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P4">Un qualsiasi altro stato <text:span text:style-name="T2"></text:span> può essere considerato come una sovrapposizione degli autostati di una grandezza <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> e può essere rappresentato da un vettore di numeri complessi <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object11" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="1.3882in" svg:height="0.3882in" draw:z-index="5"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
           <mrow>
            <mrow>
             <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
             <mi>α</mi>
             <mrow>
              <mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo>
              <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
              <mrow/>
             </mrow>
             <mrow>
              <mtable>
               <mtr>
                <mtd>
                 <mrow>
                  <mrow>
                   <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
                   <mrow>
                    <mrow>
                     <mrow>
                      <msub>
                       <mi>α</mi>
                       <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
                        <mn>1</mn>
                       </mstyle>
                      </msub>
                      <mrow/>
                     </mrow>
                     <mrow/>
                    </mrow>
                   </mrow>
                   <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
                  </mrow>
                  <mrow>
                   <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
                   <mrow>
                    <mrow>
                     <mrow>
                      <mo stretchy="false">⋮</mo>
                      <mrow/>
                     </mrow>
                     <mrow/>
                    </mrow>
                   </mrow>
                   <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
                  </mrow>
                  <mrow/>
                 </mrow>
                </mtd>
               </mtr>
               <mtr>
                <mtd>
                 <mrow/>
                </mtd>
               </mtr>
              </mtable>
              <mrow/>
             </mrow>
            </mrow>
            <mrow/>
           </mrow>
          </mstyle>
