      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>si dirà “completo”. Ad esempio le tre variabili posizione <text:span text:style-name="T1">x</text:span>, <text:span text:style-name="T1">y</text:span> e <text:span text:style-name="T1">z</text:span> costituiscono un set completo, perché data una terna di valori <text:span text:style-name="T1"><draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object47" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="1.052in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="41"><draw:object>
