      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame></text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">A questo punto scriviamo i principi generalizzati</text:p>
   <text:list text:style-name="WW8Num6">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P7">Un sistema fisico è caratterizzato dalle sue grandezze fisiche che possono essere misurate.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P7">Quando si misura una grandezza <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> sono possibili diversi risultati, ed ogni risultato ha una certa probabilità di uscire. Se dalla misura si ottiene un particolare risultato <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object66" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.35in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="60"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mover accent="true">
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
             </mover>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g= { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADzAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAmAEEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         9////yAEAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
         AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQAzAwUAAAATAlUAEwQVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
         cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAIMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABGgMBAAAAZwAIAAAAMgpgAU4AAQAAAGcA
         EAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQECAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIK
         YAGtAQEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsCFAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIi
         U3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIAAwAAAAAA
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>, il sistema si porta in uno stato tale che, se si ripete la misura di <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> si ottiene con certezza il valore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object67" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.35in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="61"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">=</mo>
             <mover accent="true">
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
             </mover>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g= { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADzAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAmAEEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         9////yAEAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
         AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQAzAwUAAAATAlUAEwQVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
         cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAIMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABGgMBAAAAZwAIAAAAMgpgAU4AAQAAAGcA
         EAAAAPsCQP4AAAAAAACQAQAAAAIEAgAQU3ltYm9sAAIEAAAALQECAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIK
         YAGtAQEAAAA9AAoAAAAmBg8ACgD/////AQAAAAAAEAAAAPsCFAAJAAAAAAC8AgAAAAABAgIi
         U3lzdGVtAAAEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIAAwAAAAAA
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>. Un tale stato viene detto autostato di <text:span text:style-name="T1">g</text:span> con autovalore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object68" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1134in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="62"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mover accent="true">
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
            </mover>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADpAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAqABEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         9////2ABAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
         AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQBnAAUAAAATAlUARwEVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
         cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAKMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABTgABAAAAZwAKAAAAJgYPAAoA/////wEA
         AAAAABAAAAD7AhQACQAAAAAAvAIAAAAAAQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAgAEAAAA8AEBAAMA
         AAAAAA==
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>.</text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="P8">2.bis<text:tab/>In generale dato un valore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object69" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1134in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="63"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mover accent="true">
           <mi>g</mi>
           <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
          </mover>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { bar  {g}}} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADpAAAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAIgAqABEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       9////2ABAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
       AAAtAQAABQAAABQCVQBnAAUAAAATAlUARwEVAAAA+wJA/gAAAAAAAJABAQAAAAQCABBUaW1l
       cyBOZXcgUm9tYW4AAKMEAAAALQEBAAgAAAAyCmABTgABAAAAZwAKAAAAJgYPAAoA/////wEA
       AAAAABAAAAD7AhQACQAAAAAAvAIAAAAAAQICIlN5c3RlbQAABAAAAC0BAgAEAAAA8AEBAAMA
       AAAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>possono esistere infiniti autostati associati a questo valore. Tuttavia è sempre possibile trovare un set di variabili completo <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object70" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.5047in" svg:height="0.222in" draw:z-index="64"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <msub>
            <mi>g</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mn>1</mn>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
           <mo stretchy="false">…</mo>
           <msub>
            <mi>g</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>n</mi>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g rSub { size 8{1} }  dotslow g rSub { size 8{n} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADAAEAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAJgAoAFEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       t////0AFAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgABUAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAA
       BAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQAACAAAADIKEAK5BAEAAABuABUAAAD7AkD+
       AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQEABAAAAPABAAAIAAAA
       MgqgAbcDAQAAAGcACAAAADIKoAFOAAEAAABnABEAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEAAAACBAIAEE1U
       IEV4dHJhAAIEAAAALQEAAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIKoAHSAQEAAABLABUAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAA
       kAEAAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQEABAAAAPABAAAIAAAAMgoQAjcB
       AQAAADEACgAAACYGDwAKAP////8BAAAAAAAQAAAA+wIUAAkAAAAAALwCAAAAAAECAiJTeXN0
       ZW0AAAQAAAAtAQAABAAAAPABAQADAAAAAAA=
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, tale che, dati gli <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> valori <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object71" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.5047in" svg:height="0.222in" draw:z-index="65"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <msub>
            <mover accent="true">
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
            </mover>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mn>1</mn>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
           <mo stretchy="false">…</mo>
           <msub>
            <mover accent="true">
             <mi>g</mi>
             <mo stretchy="false">¯</mo>
            </mover>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>n</mi>
            </mstyle>
           </msub>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { bar  {g}} rSub { size 8{1} }  dotslow  { bar  {g}} rSub { size 8{n} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADIQEAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAJgAoAFEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       t////0AFAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
       AAAtAQAABQAAABQClQBnAAUAAAATApUARwEFAAAAFAKVANADBQAAABMClQCwBBUAAAD7AiD/
       AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAoAQAAAAtAQEACAAAADIKEAK5BAEA
       AABuABUAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAoAQAAAAtAQIA
       BAAAAPABAQAIAAAAMgqgAbcDAQAAAGcACAAAADIKoAFOAAEAAABnABEAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAA
       kAEAAAACBAIAEE1UIEV4dHJhAAIEAAAALQEBAAQAAADwAQIACAAAADIKoAHSAQEAAABLABUA
       AAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEAAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAoAQAAAAtAQIABAAAAPAB
       AQAIAAAAMgoQAjcBAQAAADEACgAAACYGDwAKAP////8BAAAAAAAQAAAA+wIUAAkAAAAAALwC
       AAAAAAECAiJTeXN0ZW0AAAQAAAAtAQEABAAAAPABAgADAAAAAAA=
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, esiste un unico autostato simultaneo associato a questi valori.</text:p>
   <text:list text:continue-numbering="true" text:style-name="WW8Num6">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P7">Un qualsiasi altro stato <text:span text:style-name="T2"></text:span> può essere considerato come una sovrapposizione degli autostati simultanei di un set di grandezze <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object72" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.5047in" svg:height="0.222in" draw:z-index="66"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <msub>
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
               <mn>1</mn>
              </mstyle>
             </msub>
             <mo stretchy="false">…</mo>
             <msub>
              <mi>g</mi>
              <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
               <mi>n</mi>
              </mstyle>
             </msub>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{g rSub { size 8{1} }  dotslow g rSub { size 8{n} } } {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADAAEAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAJgAoAFEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         t////0AFAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgABUAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAA
         BAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQAACAAAADIKEAK5BAEAAABuABUAAAD7AkD+
         AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQEABAAAAPABAAAIAAAA
         MgqgAbcDAQAAAGcACAAAADIKoAFOAAEAAABnABEAAAD7AkD+AAAAAAAAkAEAAAACBAIAEE1U
         IEV4dHJhAAIEAAAALQEAAAQAAADwAQEACAAAADIKoAHSAQEAAABLABUAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAA
         kAEAAAAABAIAEFRpbWVzIE5ldyBSb21hbgAAgwQAAAAtAQEABAAAAPABAAAIAAAAMgoQAjcB
         AQAAADEACgAAACYGDwAKAP////8BAAAAAAAQAAAA+wIUAAkAAAAAALwCAAAAAAECAiJTeXN0
         ZW0AAAQAAAAtAQAABAAAAPABAQADAAAAAAA=
        </office:binary-data>
       </draw:image>
      </draw:frame>, e può essere rappresentato da un vettore di numeri complessi con <text:span text:style-name="T1">n</text:span> indici <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object73" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.9508in" svg:height="0.2854in" draw:z-index="67"><draw:object>
        <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
         <semantics>
          <mrow>
           <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
            <mrow>
             <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
             <mi>α</mi>
             <mrow>
              <mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo>
              <mo stretchy="false">≡</mo>
              <mrow>
               <mo fence="true" form="prefix" stretchy="true">(</mo>
               <mrow>
                <msub>
                 <mi>α</mi>
                 <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
                  <mrow>
                   <msub>
                    <mi>k</mi>
                    <mstyle mathsize="6pt">
                     <mn>1</mn>
                    </mstyle>
                   </msub>
                   <mo stretchy="false">…</mo>
                   <msub>
                    <mi>k</mi>
                    <mstyle mathsize="6pt">
                     <mi>n</mi>
                    </mstyle>
                   </msub>
                  </mrow>
                 </mstyle>
                </msub>
               </mrow>
               <mo fence="true" form="postfix" stretchy="true">)</mo>
              </mrow>
             </mrow>
            </mrow>
           </mstyle>
           <mrow/>
          </mrow>
          <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ \lline α \rangle  equiv  left (α rSub { size 8{k rSub { size 6{1} }  dotslow k rSub { size 6{n} } } }  right )} {}</annotation>
         </semantics>
        </math>
       </draw:object><draw:image>
        <office:binary-data>AQAJAAADswEAAAMAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
         BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADALAAuAIEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
         t////6AIAAB3AgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAACAAAkAAAD6AgAAEAAAAAAAAAAiAAQA
