      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>da sola costituisca un set completo, quindi per “completare il set” introduciamo un insieme di grandezze ausiliarie che indicheremo brevemente con un unico simbolo contratto <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr4" draw:name="Image1" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1528in" svg:height="0.25in" draw:z-index="104"/>. Per rappresentare un autostato associato ad un autovalore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object1" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1854in" svg:height="0.2457in" draw:z-index="105"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <msubsup>
           <mi>p</mi>
           <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
            <mi>x</mi>
           </mstyle>
           <mi>&apos;</mi>
          </msubsup>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { {p}} sup { &apos; } rSub { size 8{x} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAoAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAQAAAAAA
       AAAAAQAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>useremo il ket <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object2" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.5181in" svg:height="0.2457in" draw:z-index="106"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
           <msubsup>
            <mi>p</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>x</mi>
            </mstyle>
            <mi>&apos;</mi>
           </msubsup>
           <mi>,</mi>
           <msup>
            <mi>ξ</mi>
            <mi>&apos;</mi>
           </msup>
           <mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ \lline  { {p}} sup { &apos; } rSub { size 8{x} } , { {ξ}} sup { &apos; } \rangle } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAoAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAQAAAAAA
       AAAAAQAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, dove <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object3" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1291in" svg:height="0.2091in" draw:z-index="107"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <msup>
           <mi>ξ</mi>
           <mi>&apos;</mi>
          </msup>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { {ξ}} sup { &apos; }} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAoAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAQAAAAAA
       AAAAAQAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame><text:s/>è un multiindice relativo all’insieme delle grandezze ausiliarie <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object4" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1008in" svg:height="0.1854in" draw:z-index="108"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mi>ξ</mi>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ξ} {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAoAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAQAAAAAA
       AAAAAQAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Standard">(Nota che sarebbe sbagliato scrivere il ket <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr5" draw:name="Object5" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.328in" svg:height="0.2457in" draw:z-index="109"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <mrow>
           <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
           <msubsup>
            <mi>p</mi>
            <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
             <mi>x</mi>
            </mstyle>
            <mi>&apos;</mi>
           </msubsup>
           <mo stretchy="false">⟩</mo>
          </mrow>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ \lline  { {p}} sup { &apos; } rSub { size 8{x} }  \rangle } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>VkNMTVRGAQAxAAAAAAAAAAEAGwAAAAoAAAAAAAAAAAABAAAAAQAAAAEAAAABAAAAAQAAAAAA
       AAAAAQAAAA==
      </office:binary-data>
     </draw:image>
    </draw:frame>, perchè non è possibile identificare uno stato dando solo il valore <draw:frame draw:style-name="fr3" draw:name="Object110" text:anchor-type="as-char" svg:width="0.1854in" svg:height="0.2457in" draw:z-index="110"><draw:object>
      <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
       <semantics>
        <mrow>
         <mstyle mathsize="12pt">
          <msubsup>
           <mi>p</mi>
           <mstyle mathsize="8pt">
            <mi>x</mi>
           </mstyle>
           <mi>&apos;</mi>
          </msubsup>
         </mstyle>
         <mrow/>
        </mrow>
        <annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ { {p}} sup { &apos; } rSub { size 8{x} } } {}</annotation>
       </semantics>
      </math>
     </draw:object><draw:image>
      <office:binary-data>AQAJAAAD0gAAAAIAFQAAAAAABQAAAAkCAAAAAAQAAAACAQEABQAAAAEC////AAQAAAAuARgA
       BQAAADECAQAAAAUAAAALAgAAAAAFAAAADAJgAiACEgAAACYGDwAaAP////8AABAAAADA////
       t////+ABAAAXAgAACwAAACYGDwAMAE1hdGhUeXBlAABgABUAAAD7AiD/AAAAAAAAkAEBAAAA
